Key Match Events: Russell Westbrook bolted in from the 3-point line to snag an offensive rebound on a missed free throw, although it didn't count initially.
Westbrook managed to undercut Ivica Zubac and tip in DeAndre Jordan's second consecutive missed free throw, completing a four-point possession.
Michael Porter Jr. buried a 3-pointer after Peyton Watson picked Zubac's pocket, extending the Nuggets' lead to 11 points.
Westbrook finished the game with 19 points, six rebounds, and eight assists on 50% shooting.
Westbrook drew an 'and-one' foul in the post against former teammate Norman Powell and celebrated by 'rocking the baby.'
Post-Match Reflections: Russell Westbrook expressed difficulty in sleeping due to wildfires in Los Angeles, impacting his emotional state.
Westbrook emphasized his desire to bring joy to people through his performance despite the turmoil back home.
